Things @dr.chytra wishes we all knew sooner ⬇️
And trust us, once you know these—you can’t unsee them:

🧼 Wash your hands before skincare
💍 Remove rings before you wash
💸 Pricey doesn’t always mean powerful
🧻 Face towel ≠ hand towel

💡 Save this before you repeat your skincare sins again 👀
#DrChytraApproved #SkincareTruths #SimpleSkinSwitches #SkinTipsThatWork

🚨 Teen Acne? You’re not alone.
More than 80% of teenagers go through it—but here’s how to deal with it right! 💥

💧 Step 1: Use a pH-balanced, gentle cleanser
🛡️ Step 2: Target bacteria & excess oil
🧪 Step 3: Actives like Niacinamide, Salicylic Acid, Zinc & Azelaic Acid = game-changers
🧖‍♀️ Step 4: Clay mask twice a week = oil control + exfoliation
☀️ Step 5: Moisturizer + Sunscreen = non-negotiable

✨ Build your teen-friendly skincare routine today—the right way.
🎥 Watch the full Reel for details!
#TeenSkincare #AcneRoutine #ClearSkinJourney #SkinTipsForTeens

Teen Skincare: What’s safe and what’s not !
Your skin doesn’t need everything—it needs the right things. Here’s a quick guide to actives that are teen-safe ✅ and those to avoid ❌ (for now!).

✅ Safe for teens:
💧 Niacinamide – Balances oil, calms redness
💦 Hyaluronic Acid – Deep hydration without breakouts
🧼 Azelaic Acid – Clears mild acne & pigmentation gently
🔍 Salicylic Acid – Targets blackheads & unclogs pores

❌ Not for teens:
⚠️ Retinols – Too harsh, can damage skin barrier
🚫 Kojic Acid – Can cause irritation and uneven skin tone
⛔ Hydroquinone – Not safe without medical supervision

✨ Teen skin is delicate—support it, don’t stress it.

Your dermatologist knows best—and these are the 4 skincare sins @dr.chytra always avoids.
1️⃣ Sleeping with makeup on 😴 (clogs pores = acne!)
2️⃣ Skipping sunscreen ☀️ (hello, pigmentation & premature aging)
3️⃣ Not being consistent ❌ (results need routine)
4️⃣ Using harsh cleansers 🧼 (damaged barrier = irritated skin)

Watch this reel to avoid these mistakes and build a skin-loving routine 💛
#SkincareMistakes #DermatologistTips #SkinBarrier #SunscreenIsLife #SkincareRoutine #SkincareIndia #CleanserMatters #GlowingSkinTips #DrChytraSays

Skincare 101: 3 Things Every Skincare Beginner Should Know!✨
1️⃣ Don’t use a serum unless you need it
2️⃣ One product ≠ total skincare. You need a routine
3️⃣ Use evidence-based, clinically proven products
Trust me, your skin will thank you 💆‍♀️💛
#SkincareTips #BeginnerSkincare #EvidenceBasedSkincare #NoMoreSkinConfusion
